  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, pending signature)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package is issued under ProfileMinimal; a sha256 content hash is recorded but the ed25519 signature has not yet been applied — the signature workflow is pending organizational PKI provisioning. Structural integrity is therefore unverifiable until the signature field is populated. Full 13-factor assessment is included; 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). Decision: Accepted pending signature completion.",
