      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "An independent analyst must reproduce key simulation results from documented inputs; discrepancies must be within numerical noise.",
      "rationale": "No independent reproduction exercise was conducted. Simulation setup documentation exists but was not reviewed by a second qualified analyst. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The power-law hemolysis constitutive model must be evaluated against at least two alternative formulations; model-form uncertainty must be propagated to the QoI.",
      "rationale": "Only the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model was used. No alternative hemolysis model (e.g., Arora mechanistic or Taskin modified) was evaluated. Model-form uncertainty is unquantified. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs (viscosity, hematocrit, power-law exponents) must have probability distributions assigned from literature or measurement; full Monte Carlo propagation required.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo was performed on geometric tolerances only. Blood rheology parameters (hematocrit variability, viscosity temperature dependence) were held at nominal values. Input uncertainty is substantially undercharacterized. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
